The paper proposes a new representation for learning-based 3D reconstruction methods, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The approach is based on deep neural networks, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed method, which could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
